              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "63-EU-153",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.5219
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 10 g of high-purity Eu2O3",
                "powder was pressed at 980 MPa. The thickness of three",
                "samples were 0.1427 cm, 0.1718 cm, and 0.1065 cm with",
                "a diameter of 2.0 cm. Each of them was sandwiched",
                "between two neutron-flux monitor foils made of",
                "aluminum (whose purity and thickness are of 99.99%",
                "and 0.3 mm, respectively) having the same diameter as",
                "the circular sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The entire process for irradiation of all the",
                "three samples lasted 120 min with a yield about 3 to",
                "4E10 n/(4 pi*s). The three samples were placed at",
                "angles of 0, 90 or 135 deg relative to the deuterium",
                "beam direction, around the T-Ti target at distances",
                "of about 40 mm from it. After the irradiation process,",
                "three samples were cooled for 1 h, 30 h and 6.5 years."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma-ray activities of 153Sm, 150Pm, and",
                "24Na were determined by a high-purity germanium",
                "detector (ORTEC, model GEM 60P, crystal diameter:",
                "70.1 mm, crystal length: 72.3 mm, made in the USA),",
                "having a relative efficiency of about 68% and an",
                "energy resolution of 1.69 keV at 1332 keV for 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
